Test: Overflow Behavior

        /* Reset for consistency */
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        body { font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; }

        /* Test container */
        .test-container {
            width: 800px;
            height: 900px;
            border: 2px solid #333;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

        /* Test-specific CSS */
        .overflow-test {
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding: 15px;
            border: 1px dashed #999;
            background-color: white;
        }

        .test-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            color: #333;
        }

        .overflow-box {
            width: 200px;
            height: 100px;
            border: 2px solid #666;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 10px;
            display: inline-block;
            vertical-align: top;
        }

        .content {
            background-color: #ffcccc;
            padding: 5px;
            border: 1px solid #999;
        }

        .long-content {
            width: 300px;
            height: 150px;
            background-color: #ccffcc;
            border: 1px solid #666;
            padding: 10px;
        }

        /* Overflow behaviors */
        .overflow-visible {
            overflow: visible;
            background-color: #ffffcc;
        }

        .overflow-hidden {
            overflow: hidden;
            background-color: #ffccff;
        }

        .overflow-scroll {
            overflow: scroll;
            background-color: #ccffff;
        }

        .overflow-auto {
            overflow: auto;
            background-color: #ccccff;
        }

        /* Individual axis overflow */
        .overflow-x-scroll {
            overflow-x: scroll;
            overflow-y: hidden;
            background-color: #ffccaa;
        }

        .overflow-y-scroll {
            overflow-x: hidden;
            overflow-y: scroll;
            background-color: #ccffaa;
        }

        /* Text overflow */
        .text-overflow-test {
            width: 150px;
            height: 30px;
            border: 1px solid #666;
            background-color: white;
            padding: 5px;
            margin: 5px;
            display: inline-block;
            line-height: 20px;
        }

        .text-ellipsis {
            white-space: nowrap;
            overflow: hidden;
            text-overflow: ellipsis;
            background-color: #ffeecc;
        }

        .text-clip {
            white-space: nowrap;
            overflow: hidden;
            text-overflow: clip;
            background-color: #eeffcc;
        }





            Overflow: visible (default)


                    This content is larger than its container and will overflow visibly outside the bounds.





            Overflow: hidden


                    This content is larger than its container but will be clipped and hidden.





            Overflow: scroll


                    This content is larger than its container and will have scrollbars (always visible).





            Overflow: auto


                    This content is larger than its container and will have scrollbars only when needed.





            Axis-specific overflow


                    Horizontal scroll only - vertical content is clipped.




                    Vertical scroll only - horizontal content is clipped.





            Text overflow behavior

                This is a very long text that will be truncated with ellipsis


                This is a very long text that will be clipped without ellipsis




            No overflow (content fits)


                    This content fits nicely within its container bounds.







